                                            SUBWAY ENVIRONMENT SIMULATION
                                                  SIMULATION OF
                         offline-SES file for triggering error 125 in form 8D, so we can figure out how
                         to process the lines of error message after it.
                         Error 125 occurs when the route ends in one of the segments given in form 8D.
                         The program prints the error message then processes the remaining segments
                         while not using them in the route.  This is the most complex SES error to
                         process, because there is a variable count of lines after the error is
                         raised.
                         This file proceeds to the calculation after writing error 125.
                                    DESIGN TIME 1700 HRS   JULY       2029
                                                       A private, offline version of SES.  Developed
                                                       to test various program options and to learn
                                                       about SES.  Based on SES v4.1.  Credit is due to:
                                                         * Parsons, Brinckerhoff, Quade and Douglas
                                                         * De Leuw, Cather & Company
                                                         * Kaiser Engineers
                                                         * Developmental Sciences Inc.
                                                         * Graduate Aeronautical Laboratories of the
                                                           California Institute of Technology
                                                       All code modifications by Ewan Bennett.
                                                       offline-SES version 204.5
                offline-SES input file version                             204.5
                              This file has a number of bugs fixed and improved
                              printouts.  It derates jet fans in fire segments
                              according to the local air density in fire runs.
                              It prints mean temperature ratio in vent segments
                              and has a "-debug1" command-line option.
